Okay, I'm starting anew. My NEW lj is

I haven't got anything on it yet, but i should in about three days. I've already sent all my info from here to there, and so this will be my last posting.

reason of reincarnation: i hate this journal. i really do. some of the old entries just make me wanna curl up and DIE.

okay, there you have it, new LJ is go check it out in about three days (if ya still wanna be my friend, go ahead and add me. I've already added you and more. all of you, friend or not)

Okay, tis all, bye (for good).

Tee-hee...! Someone thinks my livejournal kicks ass! *.* (thanks Anonymous!)

Oh my dear lord, I haven't updated since the age of time! (I have no idea where that came from darling, it just sorta came out) Did anyone watch the Blue Collar Comedy Tour special on Comedy Central yesterday? That thing was funny as hell, especially that "Here's your sign..." thing, that was just plain hilarious. Anyone agree? Unfortunantly I only got to see the end, but I did see the Jeff Foxworthy "Totally Committed" show. That too was pretty funny. I was eating Hershey's Chocolate sauce with Swiss Miss chocolate powder ontop yesterday night while sitting out in the moon. It was half-full (I forgot the name to that, I can't think of it right now) but still pretty bright. I think that's why I missed Half of the BCCT last night.

Did anybody watch Wolf's Rain last night? Or Inuyasha? Them shows were GOOD!!!!! I'm watching Blake Clark right now on CC, but guess what?! BCCT is up next!!!!*.* (blue collar comedy tour, idiot!) I like that "Graham Norton Effect" show. Finally there's a talk show suitable for me. It has gays, sexual talk, and little games with actual celebreties you wanna hear about. I swear they based that off my wants.... (and don't you think Graham's gay, or at least a fabulous bi?)

Anyway, during the duration of my absence with internet-acces, I've been writing up on my fanfiction, now for multiple fandoms. What are they? Oh that's simple, darling: Trigun ^.^ Wolf's Rain (especially this one. Ideas are FLOWIN!!!) ^.^ X-Men (the movie. I was watching the second one the other night - at around...11:30 or somethin - and I swear the Logan/Scott and Pyro/Iceman [anyone know their names? The character names, not the actor?] just CAME) and I think that's it. Oh and HP of course. I'm already working on Chapter Three of PAC, I've alrready got some cool ideas for it, I'm just having trouble putting it all on paper.

I gotta go now, bye!

Finally got around to posting my new story. Follow the link on the bottom to read, the summary is inside. The rateing is 'E' as of now, might change later though.

New Story

Okay, well, that's all i have to say. I would have posted this link with the previouse entry, but it has no hyper link, so that sucks major arse. Bye.

Incase ya ever wanna make me.

 

Okay, enough with that, now, about yesterdays QAF show. WONDERFUL!!!!!!!!!!!!! OMG! Now I just love Justing even more!! *.* And before I thought he was kinda annoying (though will and have not EVER liked the Brian/Micheal pairing. Euchh...) I mean, did you see him??? Just the way he scolded Brian like that! "You get your ass in bed, you son of a bitch, and eat your fucking chicken soup!!" LOVELY!!!! But you know, I think the reason why he was so anoying at first was because of his hair. Didn't really like it. Not even when he shaved it like Tom Felton and that other "Pink Posse" leader dude that got a hand-job from Jus after holding the gun. But now his hair looks GREAT!

Oh I so can't wait till the next episode! *squee!* And EMMET!!!! Did you see him and that football (I hate american football. Never did like it.... never will) player??? I love that pairing now! (The only reason why I'm okay with his cheating on his wife is because a.) either it with a man,or b.) the wife was a really mean bitch) Oh! And speaking of pairings....

  • Tommy Dawkins/Merton Dingle - Big Wolf on Campus
  • Tsume/Toboe - Wolf's Rain
  • Hige/Kiba - Wolf's Rain
  • Inu-Yasha/Sessho-Maru - InuYasha
  • Inu-Yasha/Kagome (a litle bit) - Inuyasha
  • Sesshoumaru/Kagome (better than above) - Inu-Yasha
  • Sango/Miroku- Inuyasha
  • Harry Potter/Draco Malfoy - Harry Potter
  • Marcus Flint/Oliver Wood - Harry Potter
  • Fred Weasley/George Weasly - Harry Potter
  • Ron Weasly/Ginny Weasley - HP
  • Bill/Charlie (weasley) - HP
  • Ron Weasley/Pansy Parkinson - HP
  • Hermione/Malfoy - HP
  • Blaise/Seamus - HP
  • Aubrey/Jessica - Demon In My View
  • Tom Felton/Daniel Radcliffe - RPS (a little bit)
  • Dorothy/Big O robot controler (dont know his name) - Big O (though I hardly watch this show)
  • Vash/Male OC - Trigun (don't know why. Just think he'd make and excelletn gay pairning)
  • Vash/Merill[sp?] - Trigun
  • Emmet/Football player - Queer As Folk (QAF)
  • Brian/Justin - QAF
  • Micheal/Ted - QAF
  • Hunter/OC - QAF (to be honest, I don't care if it's male or female. Hmm, guess thts just the way I think...)

And that's all I can think of for now. Too tired to do anything else exept write this:

  1. Hige/Kiba because it's better than Kiba/Cheza or Hige/Blue or anything else
  2. A little Inu-Kag because the way he treats her there sbound to be a fatal heartbreak that'll leave Kag to go to Seshie and act like Rin's mother
  3. Sango/Miroku, you can just see the love right there
  4. No Percy pairings because I hate percy. He can just go along and fuck his little Penelope Ravenclaw for all i care
  5. A little bit for Tom 'n' Dan because, well, I don't really like Dan too much. At least appearance wise. But I do like his personality. (at least from what i've seen from him in all the interviews an all. He is an actor after all, you never know...)

Das it. Gu-bye.

Does anybody know of the band, The Azoic? I swear they're hte best, even if I oly heard of like, the beginign to about three songs.

Okay, about "Preliminary", I'm not going to have the band Sigur Ros metioned in it because, well, I've only heard one and half songs from 'em, the website I've gone to (www.sigurros.com) is slow, meaning that every song I go to takes forever to buff, and only plays like two secods beore it has to fully buff all over again. A real bitch I tell ya. And besides that, my internet (AOL) is getting cut off because it's too expensive. It's supposed to by the end of this month, but thankgod they said that my brother isn't going to leave for college and leave me without intenet. So that's good. But I might not be able to post for a while (that and because i'm grounded for the whole "summer school" business *grumbles*)

And I'm not gonna mention the Quizno subs thing on Wiess's perspective. (I was hungry then, and I was typing pretty fast while doing so. Lately I've come to not eating for ling periods of time and eating fattning foods when I do. Right now, and yesterday, I have a HUGE craving for cookies. Peppridge Farms cookies to be exact. Oh! I saw the commercial {never see that commercial when hungry} and I was on the floor drooling. I asked my mom to get tem, she said she will, and came back home empty save of milk. That's not exactly "cookie". But oh well. I've had a good day so far {since I had pancakes for breakfast. Made em myself, so you can bet they were really thick but in regular size. Very puffy and not burned. And buttery. *yummm*} that's being ruined by my mum constantly bugging me to clean my fuckin room. I retort wiht an irritable "whatever" and wait until the next ten minutes to repeat the same pointles actions. She knows I'm not gonna clean my room, so why ask?)

Okay, that's all for now.

Azoic rules,

and so do I.

(why do I always get suffed after one pancake, and get full after two to the point of puking? It ALWAYS hapens and I hate it. Maybe I should just stick with waffles? They are good, but you can't rip em up and dip em into a dish of syrup. {maple is the best})

Listening to the end of "Show Me Love" by t.A.T.u.; looking at a Pyramid Collection catalogue; and typing in this hopefully long and rambling journal entry; now listening to "30 Minutes" by the same artist as above; am I.

Okay, well, am still waiting for an e-mial by Izterblith (or Izzy-chan, whichever...) and I am still holding the grudge of what my mother did to me yesterday.

Okay, originally, I was just not gonna go to school yesterday, but the day before, my mom got a call from the school, saying that I was going to have to go to summer school. I only failed 3 classes this time, two of them major. Last year, I failed Gym, Biology, History, English, and Math. This year, I only failed History, Science, and Gym. Pretty good on account of last year.

Now, last year, all my mom basicly did was slap me twice, one on my arm and once on my face, cry, yell at me, adn all that jazz. But this year, I went to school (against my will, I'll have you know) grabbed the fucking forms for SS, went home when the long and hot day was over, and fell asleep. Took a long, long nap (from 2:30 to 7:30 PM long) woke up, waited two seconds for her to come home, gave her the papers, and basicly went on the computer.

I was about open a window, when my stomach rumbled and realised I was hungry. so, turning off the screen since something told me I was not gonna get out of her room for a very long time, I walked over.

She was watching the news, sitting on her footchest or whatever it's called. And she's always telling ME to get off that.... (damn hypocrite)

Anyway, she started to talk all this bunch of junk (apparetnly she was drunk) then she started crying. "Why do I have to cry - for this? Tell me, Veronica, why? Why do I have to cry?" and I'm thinking, 'don't then. It's easy, really. Just stop crying.' but apparetnly she doesn't have my givt of random apathy that I cherish so.

Then she came down on her knees in front of me, ans said, "200 dollars. I have to pay - $200! How am I going to do that?!" really I thought it wasn't that much. And if she could pay 335 dollars for some damn thing my brother wants, she certainly could pay 200 dollars for me. So I said, "Why don't you just split it with Papi?" (we're spanish, so my dad is called Papi even though we speak english)

She started mumblng some shit I really couldn't understand, but I did understand her middle finger standing erect in front of me. "Once. i only hit you once, Veronica (she really didn't, but I guess that doesn't count, does it? >.<) Can you tell me why?" and then I put a fake smile, falsly cheery, and said, "Because you're ashamed of me?" and you know what she said? She siad, "That is not why. Why do you have to challenge (well, wiht her accent, it came out more as whah-ee doo yoo haove too shallenge peepole la-eek thaut? Whaee?) people like that? why?"

"I don't chalenge things except for their views on gays. Is that a problem?" I said glaring at her. But she never answered. Instead, she stood up agian, and said, "I'm going to have a yard sale. I'm going to sell all the CD's you have, and that is how you are going to pay off that 200 dollars. From now on, you will have no rights. You will not have any CD's; no music, no Tv, no computer, no books, no posters on the wall, Nuzza (did you know that she named him? Yeah, it's my pet, but I didn't get to name him. I was going to name him something like Fafnir or somehitng, but I never got to)is going to be fat like mommy (she calls me my iguana's mom. I'm really not, because, well, I'm not an iguana.) Mush (the dog that isn't exactly mine. It's not my job to feed her) is going to be fed, your room will be cleaned, and you will give me A's. I am going to go on the internet (she never goes on the computer! How the hell does she think she'll be able to go ont the interenet?) And sell all your CD's. I'm going to put up a sign that says 'Daughter who fails, mother to sell all her CD's to pay for summer school'." And then before she can continue, I politely interrupted her. "Mom! Do you honestly think that anyone would wanna buy something off of you?"

"I'm not done talking!!" so I tuned her out until she did finish. then I stood up, ans said, "well, I just came here to say that I was hungry, but I guess that's not currently on your mind, is it?" and I left the room. I made some food for meself (really, I can cook, but I'm not exactly allowed to since it isn't my kitchen)

After that, since my brother was on the computer now because "no one was on it", I went to bed....again. grabbing my iguana off the curtain pole thingy, I locked my door (even though I'm not allowed to. I'm not even allowed to have candles in my room!) and fell asleep.

About three hours later, my insomnia was finally kicking in, and I got up and out of my room. My ugly mother was in her ugly blue bathrobe that really belongs to Kenny (step dad that I feel uncomfortable around and really don't like) was prowling arund, too.

So, ignoring her, I walked up to the frige, and got a drink of pink lemondae from Crystal Light. She walked into the kitchen too.

Taking my cup, I walked to the computer, whcich was right in the room next to the kitchne. I turned it on.

"What are you doing?"

"What doesn it look like?"\

Dammit! My brother's kicking me off. I'll continue later, bye.

God damn it! I hate that!!!! Why doesn't it _ever_ work??? >.< *sigh* okay, here it is, the part that I said was really random and apparetnly didn't work *grumbles about how stupid some things are/work*.

Okay. Found the latest news on the Graduation fiasco thing an' all. Apparently, it is to be held on Friday, at the McDanough highschool gym (or is it something else...? Auditorium? That would make sense, but I don't know if they have one or not.), and is to be lasting from 7:00 through 8:30. Disgusting, isn't it? I don't care what my mother says, I am not going, whether she likes it or not. It's her choice to go, not mine. Whether she chooses to go alone, is up to her. You know, maybe see the other kidles go an' all. Go with Kenny...

Speaking of Kenny, Kinney. I absolutely can't believe what happened yesterday night on QAF. Brian did not do that. Nope, nope nope! I refuse to believe that MY sweet Justinlovin caring BRIAN, did that. No! Uh-uh! (can one tell that I am currently on denial here?) Oh god, but from what I gather, this has happened before, wiht one Ethan, I presume? I've only seen the 4th season of QAF, so I wouldn't know, therefore am traumatized by the Justin/Brian brakeup.

Question. Am I the only person who doesn't like the Micheal/Brian pairing? I seem to be, because on ff.net, a lot of people do. And that's not what I wanna read. I wanna read the Justin/Brian fics, and maybe a Micheal/Ben with Hunter (NOT as a threesome! Euww!!!>.<) on the side here-and-there. And the B/J fics I have read, are all sweet and fluffy where B tells J he loves him. Yeah, it's nice once in a while, BUT NOT EVERY FUCKIN TIME!!! I'd rather have QAF fics NOT be AU's or fluffys or Micheal/Brian! (like I said, a BJ fluffy fic here or there once in a while is nice, BUT NOT ALL THE FUCKIN TIME!>.<)

that was really random... but oh well. Deal.

Hmm, JessieCollet... That's actually not too bad1 At least it's someone I know and shares the same undying love for *bites lips and smiles sweetly* TOME FELTON!!!!! ^.^

Okay, anyway, Awards Ceremony was today, and it was boring as hell. Heck, my brother's graduation was more lively than this! It was too upsetting, but the only good part was that we got to miss some classes, and that's always good, right? Right.

Oh! Guess what? I'm a new fan of Tommy/Merton slash pairing! It's from the nowunaired show, Big Wold On Campus, and it only took me one fic to convince me so.

I'm not gonna link though, because it wasn't that big. (that and I have no idea where it is) Or that great.

Gotta go, bye.

(P.S., this font-colour is in white, so if you click on the link, you'll have to highlight the text so that you'll be able to see it, kay?)

My Brother's graduation was today, and it was quite boring. I have to say, I expected it to be both faster and slower than it was. Slower fo rthe actual ceremony, and faster for the coming out of my brother (not homosexually. As in coming out of the building; Prentice Hall or something like that, at the Showcase Arena. My mother was stinking and my father's breath smelled.) My mum went off searching for him, and it was like a half hour later before we finally found her. She hugged him, I was forced into a stupid picture, and basicly had an uncomfortable day. (I had to wear a dress. A DRESS!!! Everyone else who was young wore freakin' casual clothing!!! But...I wasn't the only one. There was this younger kid who wore a very nice dress,  might I add. So I wasn't totally pissed. But at least I know what I'm gonna do with that dress! I'm gonna where it for MY graduation, except instead of the black leggings and chungky heels I wore, I'm gonna wear my jeans and my Vans! *.* See how you like that, momma!!>:]) But as soon as I got home, I changed into my comfort clothes (jeans, black t-shirt, Vans or Addidas [mainly Vans, though. Addidas I have are kinda old...])

My dad's leaving tommorrow, but I'm gonna get to see him agian in about three weeks, where I get to fly to Florida and see my second family! ^.^ OOh, I can't wait to see my little brothers!! Oh their gonna be soo cute! One is like Five or six and the other is about one. The youngest had a hole in his heart, so he has a perminant scar across his chest. In my opinion, it looks really cool...

I'm mad about my pool. They're startin' to clean it, and when they did, they put so much chlorine in it that all the cute little tadpoles are now DEAD! >.< I literally held like fifteen dead of them in my hand. I took them out of the water and put them in the ground, I just didn't want them to be dissolved into acid-like water when they're in such a fragile condition. I mean BABIES! DEAD! AND THEY'RE NOT EVEN HUMAN!!!!!!!!! I wouldn't be as mad, if they were human. Humans deserve to die, I deserve to die! With all the hate and choas an EVERYTHING!!!!This isn't the world we were meant to live in, this is a hell WE created, and nature's only trying to get back her revenge. And you know what? It's beautiful. (I'm talking about storms/hurricane/atmospheric openings/hurricanes/earthquakes/low percentage of safe water to drink from/global warming/tital waves...)

Whew! Well, that's all I can think of, except Oh! 'Fore I forget. Yesterday, it was raining. there was some sky-lightning and thunder, but it wasn't anything serious. In fact, it was gorgeuos. So naturally, I wanted to stand out in it. My mother didn't quite agree with that. We got into a rather silly argument, me being the rebellious teen an' all. But I was so mad! She doesn't give me ANY privacy; she searches/cleans my room when it's TOTALLY fine; when I go to the mall which really isn't that often, she wont let me go ALONE!!!!!!!!! AND!whenever I try something on, I HAVE TO SHOW HER!!!! I REALLY don't feel comfortable doing that!! So, I did the stupidest thing ever. I waved her off, rolling my eyes, and went to the backdoor, the one where we usually let Mush (my dog) out. I unlocked it, ran straight to the pool, crouched by the side of it (it was nighttime, so I have no idea how I could have done that without tripping or hitting the fence. I'm just glad it was open...) thrusted my hand in and let the rain wahs over me. Mum didn't follow me, thank god, and it felt totally good. The rain was pefect, and the thunder/lightning was just beautiful. However, when I got back, she slapped my twice (hard) and yelled at me. Again, she implied the fact that I'm an embarrassment. She doesn't exactly say it, and I don't even think she knows it, but if you listen, she says it.

Okay, well, that's all for now. M'still trying to figure out how I'm gonna put what's in my head to words so that I can show you guys, but I'm having MAJOR writer's block right now. Also got the t.A.T.u. CD and Dimmu Borgir, Death Cult Armaggedon. It's really good, especially the fourth song. And the t.A.T.u. CD is just AWESOME!!!!! I love every song of it (except for the last one) Gotta go now, see ya.

Okay! Well, a bunch of news today. Made a new friend today. Her name's Tammei (i think. thats what i heard her say that that was how to spell her name. but then again i couldnt really hear her well cause of all the noise emmanating from leeana) and do you wanna know why we clicked so well and talked practically the entire four hours? Because we both have the same sense of humour. See, in my so-called "group of friends" (they've "abondoned" me cause we were just too different. we have a few laughs, but I've made new [and better] friends. Of course we do have a few laughs together, and I've recently disvovered Jessica also thinks two really hot guys making out is, well, hot! I was so happy that day, and Christina too! she likes it as well *.*)

See, I'm sorta the "perverted" one, because I crack out jokes or "pervert" something they say, or I say something and they automatically think I'm saying the wrong thing. It's very anoying because they never seem to take me seriously, and so therefore can never show my really quiet, shy, and cold uncaring self. Anyway, on to example. Once, I said, "What are you _doing_ to that hotdog???" to Jessica, and everyone started lauging but then said, "Verooonnniiccaaaaaa!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!" and I can only grin and shrug sheepishly. (she was taking a HUGE bite out of her hotdog, so they thought I thought she was deep-throating it, when really I thought she was trying to swallow it whole. That thought never even crossed my mind.)

So anyway, today we had some kind of outing for middle-school seniors (I failed fifth grade, so I was like fifteen <well, fifteen in June, but that's not really very far, so...>. some there [like Brandon and Chris] were sixteen! So I'm not that embarassed) and we just sat there, me kinda sticking out. A little whiles later, and some hamburgers eaten by my friends (I didn't eat until much later. And even then it was only a small bag of Fritos and a bottle of water. Besides, lines where TOO big and there was no CHEESE on the BURGERS!!!!!!!!!!! I HAVE TO HAVE CHEESE ON MY BURGER OR I'M NOT EATIN' IT, DAMMIT!!!!!!!! >.<) and sodas drunken by them (i din't drink anything either. too big a line) Tammy came by; me and Jackie were just sitting there, and she must have spotted her while bored since Hanah didn't pay her library fine and couldnt go.

So yeah, she meandered on over, talked to Jackie and me, then we stood up, ready to walk around. we reached the midsection between the kickball field and the tennis courts. She wanted to play kickball but there wasnt a ball (it was used to be played soccer which I was very pleased to see) and we (meaning my and Jackie) didn't want to play, just walk around. So she gave in, changing her mind, and chose to sit in the bleachers with us. we started talking some more (i don't really remember what, though) when the others came by (Jessica; Jessica <there's 2 of 'em>; Heather; Jamie; Christina; LeeAnna (I really don't know how to spell that>) after a while, Jackie and Tammy walked a few steps up and were talking. I just sat there, listening to the other 5 talk.

Jackie and Tammy gathered some honeysuckle, and after a bit, I got like two of them for my own. They were covered in bugs! I can't believe I didnt see it before when I ate one without realising it! *eww!!* but it was still good *disgusting self out here*

After a tidbit, Jackie, me, and Tammy decided to play a little game of tag. So, I was ununanimously picked first, and taged Tammy lethargically on the shoulder. I was like "Okay. Tag - you're it" and we made a little joke by slow-motion running. Then it started to get a little faster. Tammy taged Jacki whom tagged me, so then i walked-chased Tammy (me plan was to go after her, then backfire and go to jackie when she least expects it. but it didn't turn out that way. I wounded up just going after Tammy) *and it was SO funny!* and she was headed for the dick! (see, heather and I don't know who else drew a giant penis in the sands of the kickball field. If you stand in the very top bleacher, you could see it!) so i told her so. I said, "Hey, you're steppin' on the dick, there!" and she slowed down as if studying it up-close-and-personal. Uh-Uh! So a ran the rest of the few steps, shoved her lightly for good measure, and said, "Tag! you're it, bitch!" and ran toward the bleacher. Since I've just tagged her, she seemed to think like me and went after Jacki instead, just to be fair so that she wont feel left out.

They went all over the place. So I sat back on the bleacher. They came over, and were running aroudn the bleacher. Eventually (Jacki was it now) I decided to help her out. So, when she came by, I held out my hand and said "I'll get her for ya" and so she slapped it like a high-five, and when Tammy came around, thinking Jackie was still "it", i tagged her shoulder and said, "You're it!!"

After that, I had to go to the "little gurls room". turns out I was right after Tammy. She came out thinking I was about to tag her when really I had to Pee!  I came out, and headed over to the bleacher, but didn't have to. They (and Leeana who was acting severly high) were twirling in front of Ms. Lily's trailer/class room (my school has some class rooms out in the trailers. 8th grade only, though) I didn't join them, though, becasue Leeana nearly knocked me over when she twirled into me. I pretended to smakc her and say "Snap out of it!" like Cher did in that movie, what ever it's called....

Okay fastforward......:

This is just a little dialogue between H and D. Please read and review. It'll make me happy since I've a gass-pressure stomach ache that hurts like a bitch, and a sore throat that hurts when I cough, swallow, sneeze, and stretch my neck up. 

*from the living room, after Harry plops down on the beige leather sofa, picking up a magazine.*

"No primping, Draco!!!!!!!!" he calls, trying to prevent from being late - or 'fashionably late' as Draco likes to call it - for their date/dinner reservations for their anniversary. It was going to be in their favourite restaurant, which just os happens to be the exact same one they had their first date in, making it that much more special and romantic and meaningful.

"Uhh! But Harry!!!!" Draco whined from thier bedroom, fixing himself up for tonight; trying to make himself look extra nice for his lover on a true night like this. Even though Harry's always telling him that he doesn't need to primp since he's already beautiful to Harry, Draco still likes to primp. It was fun; just as girls like to dress up, he liked to primp. (In which his primping is not much different from their dressing up to tell you the truth.)

"No, Draco. We're going to be late agian if you do. Just hurry up and get your scrumptious tight arse over here, gorgeous." Harry smirked at the sharp "Harry!" Draco had hissed. Theywere both prudes in their own times, more often when the other wasn't, like right now, balancing that perfectly. But Draco needed to hurry up! In Harry's eyes, Draco was perfect, the most beautiful person he has ever seen; and he's seen a lot of people! It was a lost cause to perfect perfection. And that's just what Draco's attempting to do! it would be impossible! 

 About five minutes passed and Harry was begining to wonder about Draco. So wiht that in mind, he got up off the couch and headed towards his room. The door was wide open, so there was no need to do anything to it.

And what do you know? Draco was standing right there in front of their full-length mirror, primping.

Harry sighed loudly, startling the pale, blonde Adonis. "Jesus Christ, Harry! Don't do that!" he exclaimed. He never did liked getting startled, and Harry had a nasty habit of doing that.

Harry chuckled before saying, "Come on beautiful, you're gonna make us late again." and left the door, knowing Draco will follow.

As expected, he did, but not without a few corrections. "It's fashionably late, and we're not going to. Not without a little hocus pocus!" So grabbing their coats, Harry grabbed Draco around the waist and roughly pulled Draco towards him. "Come on, beautiful." "Alright, sexy." and Harry pulled him into a rough kiss while they apparated to the restaurant.

Okay. First story posted up here, and I'm kinda nervous. I really hope this works, cause if not, then I'm going to be really frustrated. Okay, so here goes...

This one's about Harry and Draco (obviously) together in their apartment. This is an AU fic, os that means there is no war, no Hogwarts, no Tom or Voldie, and no rivalry whatsoever between them.

 

"Harry?" no answer. "Harry!" Draco jabbed a finger into Harry's rib sharply in the hopes of waking him.

"Hmm..." Harry grunted, a vocal reflex to the sharp poke in the side.

"Harry!" another shove, this time succeeding in waking up the sleeping man. "Wha-at???" he groaned sleepily, scowling from being woken up at an ungodly hour.

"I'm cold. You took up all the blankets again." Draco said softly, hoping to get warm again. Harry smiled, "Oh. Sorry." and opened up the blankets, patting the warm space next to him softly. Draco scooted in happily, snuggling his back to Harry's chest. When he got in, Harry closed the blanket over them, putting his leg over Draco's thigh and an arm around Draco's chest, holding him possessively. Draco smiled, feeling Harry kiss the side of his head and giving him a light squeeze, causing Draco to sigh contentedly.

"Love you." Harry said, "Love you, too." Draco replied, squeezing Harry's arm a bit before settling in and falling back asleep.
